President Biden has authorized an increase in federal funding for debris removal and emergency protective measures in Florida following the Surfside Building Collapse. The federal share for these costs has been increased to 100% of the total eligible costs for a continuous period of 30 days beginning June 24, 2021. This assistance is provided under the emergency declaration issued for Florida on June 25, 2021. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.